   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>News Roundup:</big></font>

   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>Mobhunter Sunday Brunch</big></font>

   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Kohath</font>

   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">01/27/2002 11:40 AM CST</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText"><big>Shoot Your Foot Off</big><p><a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=19438">Shamans have noticed</a> new messages while attempting to hurt themselves.  In certain cases, harming yourself seems to have been made more difficult.<p><big>Snakes</big><p>With Luclin's third month of release approaching, the Ssra Temple has shaped up as the favored lunar raiding spot for uber guilds.  Unfortunately, the zone is apparently unfinished.<p><a href="http://www.tritonguild.com/">Triton of Povar</a> recently visited the temple and found the key to unlock the Emporer.  You can imagine <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=9555.topic">their disappointment</a> when the door didn't open.  The GM later confirmed that the lock was broken.  His imperial majesty still waits within the chamber.  A technician has been dispatched to repair the door.<p>Meanwhile, on another server, Legacy of Steel has had better luck with the doors.  They killed Xerkizh the Creator and the Glyphed.  The received some <a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/">oddly restricted loot</a>.<p><big>The Undiscovered Country</big><p>Uber guilds are continually searching out new frontiers.  As the conquest of the snake nears its completion, there are hints of the eventual discovery of a passage to Vex Thal.  We at Mobhunter are largely in the dark about Vex Thal, but <a href="http://www.psyborg.com/screenshots.html">these screenshots</a> (<a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3429.topic">more here</a> and <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=9604.topic">here</a>) have recently appeared showing us something of the zone.<p><big>The Tip of the Iceberg</big><p>Turning from places I've never been to equipment I'll never have, I've recently come across <a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmmrpgdiscussionmonks.showMessage?topicID=5041.topic">this post on EQ Monks</a>.  There appears to be more to <i>Recommended Level</i> than a simple recommendation.  It's not certain, but this hints at a whole new system of anti-twinking code in EverQuest.<p>Personally, I like twinking, but it doesn't seem out of order for there to be a few more restrictions.  Whatever the merits of the new anti-twinking system, Verant is to be cheered for actually giving us some numbers to work with rather than &quot;it works better when you reach the recommended level, somehow worse until then&quot;.  On the other hand, jeers to Verant for not being more up front about the whole system.</font>
  </td>
 </tr>
